 Martin Luthor King <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#b9a1d0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub98.ezboard.com/breligiousdebate60574.showUserPublicProfile?gid=luvthatdyl>LuvThatDyl</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Member</span><br>  Posts: 178<br> <font color=#3333ff>(6/23/03 2:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   hate crimes</span><hr size=1> I have that same dream, but we will never achieve it if we have seperate rules for seperate groups of people.  Laws need to be created with our minds instead of our emotions.  As a member of the second most hated group in this country, I would hate to see people turn a blind eye to prejudice and the ways in which we can prevent it.  I just don't feel this legislation is the way to do it.  I fear that special legislation and special rules concerning minorities will just divide this nation even further apart.  When a white man sees his attacker get less of a sentence than that attacker of a black man, the white man will feel some contempt for the black man, even if he never had a racist emotion run through his body his whole life.  He will say to himself &quot;it isn't fair that I couldn't see the same justice just because I wasn't part of that group&quot;.  We can't truly start looking past someone's color if we have laws being thrown in our face that constantly remind eachother of our differences.  The backbone of education against prejudice is teaching people that we are all the same underneath.  How can we all feel the same underneath if we all have a different peace of mind in regard to the laws that protect us?  Only when all the same laws apply to all the same people will we truly feel that we are the same inside and out.<br>
<br>
As for cross burning and such, I believe that burning anything on someone's property should be considered a major offense due to the dangers involved.  If we want to step up the severity of burning objects and vandalizing people's property due to prejudice, then we should consider doing so across the board.  It takes just as much energy to have to repaint a vandalized church that it does to repaint a vandalized synagogue.  A plain burning stick has the same potential to burn down the house of a white Christian family as a burning cross does to burn down the house of a Muslim family.  When a crime is committed, everyone suffers the same in the end.<br>
<br>
Stacey <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showMessageRange?topicID=155.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showPrevMessage?topicID=155.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showNextMessage?topicID=155.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=155.topic&index=22><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.emailToFriend?topicID=155.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.threadControl?topicID=155.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/bluesparty/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=155.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub98.ezboard.com/freligiousdebate60574frm2.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=155.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form acti